PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY

IT Professional with over 12 years of experience, including 5 years in Cloud AWS and DevOps, and 3 years in Linux Administration. I specialize in automation, cloud infrastructure, and system optimization, with a proven track record in designing and implementing CI/CD pipelines to enhance deployment efficiency and system reliability.

Cloud Expertise: Proficient in managing AWS Cloud Services (EC2, IAM, S3, VPC, RDS, CloudFormation) to deliver scalable, secure, and cost-effective solutions while ensuring high availability and performance.
CI/CD Proficiency: Expertise in building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines using tools like Jenkins and Maven, streamlining deployment processes across development, testing, and production environments.
Infrastructure Automation: Automated infrastructure provisioning with Terraform and CloudFormation, reducing manual intervention and improving scalability and consistency in deployments.
Containerization Skills: Experienced in orchestrating Docker containers with Kubernetes, ensuring scalability, fault tolerance, and high availability of containerized applications.
Linux Administration: Strong background in Linux Administration, specializing in system hardening, patching, and troubleshooting to maintain secure and reliable environments.
Scripting & Automation: Skilled in scripting with Bash and Python to automate processes and enhance operational efficiency.
Technical Support Excellence: Proven track record in providing technical support for test equipment and network troubleshooting, achieving a 30% reduction in downtime and improving system uptime.
Collaborative Approach: Adept at working closely with development and operations teams to optimize workflows and drive improvements in cloud infrastructure performance and efficiency.


