PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY

IT Professional with over 12 years of experience, including 5 years in Cloud AWS and DevOps, and 3 years in Linux Administration. I specialize in automation, cloud infrastructure, and system optimization, with extensive hands-on experience in designing, automating, and optimizing CI/CD pipelines using tools like AWS, Terraform, Ansible, Jenkins, Docker, and Kubernetes.
Proficient in managing AWS Cloud Services (EC2, IAM, S3, VPC, RDS, CloudFormation) to deliver scalable, secure, and cost-effective cloud solutions while ensuring high availability and performance.
Expertise in building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines, utilizing tools like Jenkins and Maven, and ensuring smooth deployment processes across development, testing, and production environments.
Automated infrastructure provisioning using Terraform and CloudFormation, improving scalability and reducing manual intervention and errors in deployment processes.
Strong background in Linux Administration, specializing in system hardening, patching, and troubleshooting to maintain robust and secure environments.
Experience in orchestrating Docker containers with Kubernetes, ensuring scalability, fault tolerance, and high availability of containerized applications.
Skilled in scripting with Bash and Python for automation, infrastructure management, and improving operational efficiency.
Proven track record in providing technical support for test equipment and network troubleshooting, reducing downtime by 30% and improving system uptime.
Adept at collaborating with development and operations teams to streamline workflows and optimize cloud infrastructure for enhanced performance and efficiency.


